# magiclists

Vanilla JS ES modules + plain CSS. Client-only; primary data via `js/api.js` → `localStorage` (`matrix_database`). Cloud backup and drawing data use additional keys. Entry: `index.html` → `js/app.js`. UI brand: **magicNotes**; repo id: **magiclists**. No React/TS/bundler unless asked.

**Architecture:** `app.js` orchestrates; modules use `window` CustomEvents (`namespace:action`). Item CRUD through `API` only; UI mutations emit `item:mutation_requested` (handled in `app.js`). Tools: `js/tools/*.js` with `@tool` header + `init(mount)`; `stop` hook auto-runs `build-tools-list.ps1` when tools change. Board views: grid + freeform only (columns view removed). Workspace modes: `notes` | `drawing` (magicCanvas).

**Before editing:** grep/read existing patterns in the area you touch and its callers. Minimal diff; no dead code or half-migrations. Reuse `CARD_ICONS` / `ACTION_ICONS` from `js/icons.js` (`ui.js` re-exports). Note cards/checklists/sheets: start in `noteSurface.js`.

**Design:** Minimal, lightweight, smooth, modern, compact. Dark default; use CSS variables and existing theme pickers. Reuse classes (`.btn`, `.card-act`, `.collapsable-*`, `.overlay`) — ask before inventing new ones. Modular files; same tropes across tiles, editor, sidebar, tools. Match existing interaction patterns (hover, overlay, persistent). UX first.

**Architecture map (generated):** See `.cursor/rules/magiclists-architecture.mdc` — auto-refreshed by Cursor `stop` hook (PowerShell, no Node). Source of truth: `@css` / `@module` / `@tool` headers + `index.html` CSS links. Grep sibling CSS files before adding cross-cutting selectors.

**On create (same turn, mandatory):** new `css/*.css` → `@css` header + `index.html` link; new domain JS → `@module` header; new tool → `@tool` header. Do not assume the user will run scripts — hooks rebuild the map when the turn ends.

**CSS lifecycle:** New domain → new file + `@css` + `index.html` link. Extend smallest owning file (check generated map). Shared tokens → `css/base.css` only. Merge: union `@css` metadata, remove link, delete file.

**JS lifecycle:** Add `@module` when a file becomes a primary domain owner (not every helper). Extract from `ui.js`/`editor.js`: tag new file, list in old file's `related`.

**Note footer:** `.editor-meta-wrap` → `.editor-meta-row--footer.editor-meta-row--inline`. One CSS block in `shell.css`; single-line `0.48rem` × `--note-font-scale`. Do not add per-view font-size overrides unless user explicitly asks.

**Deliver:** concise, no preamble; audit shared styles/components for regressions across board, editor, sidebar, calendar, tools, weather, radio, TV, cloud, file cabinet, drawing, sheet templates.

## Git / GitHub (required — magiclists workspace only)

This section applies only in chats opened for this repo. Do not use this commit prompt in other projects.

Never commit or push unless the user explicitly agrees.

**End-of-turn commit prompt — mandatory:** If this conversation turn created or modified any project files, the assistant's final lines MUST ask whether to commit. Do not skip this when wrapping up, summarizing, or saying work is done. Do not commit silently.

Prompt format (last thing in the message):
1. One-line summary of what changed
2. Ask: **commit only**, **commit + push to origin**, or **skip**?

Skip the prompt only when the turn was read-only (no file edits) or the user already answered for the current changes.

When the user agrees to commit:
1. `git status` + `git diff` to verify scope
2. Include `.cursor/rules/magiclists-architecture.mdc` (and `js/tools/registry.js` if tools changed) if hooks refreshed them this turn
3. Stage only relevant files (never `.env`, credentials, or accidental junk)
4. Commit with a concise message (why, not a file list) matching recent repo style
5. Push only if they also want push (or ask again after commit)

If push fails (auth, hook, conflict), report the error and fix or ask before continuing. Do not force-push to `main`.
